 <purpose>This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the definition of  assembly_feature_relationships and provides general representations for relationships between
component parts within an assembly model. The distinction between assembly, subassembly and component part is context dependent.
 
 </purpose>

<inscope>
  <li>the association of shape aspect relationship with its representation;
 the association of instanced assembly feature relationship with its representation;

  </li>
  <li>the association of instanced assembly feature relationship with its representation;</li>
  <li>positioned assembly_feature_relationshipes, defined in three-dimensional model space;</li>  
  <li>the representation of the fixed constituent which plays the anchor role in the assembly model.</li>
  
 </inscope>

 <outscope>
  <li>product structure configurations of assemblies and their constituents.</li>
  
 </outscope>

  
 

